.SH SYNOPSIS
.sp
diffusion MRI based fiber tracking using parallel transport tractography
.SH USAGE
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.nf
.ft C
trekker [ options ]
.ft P
.fi
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.SH DESCRIPTION
.sp
To track fibers using a diffusion MRI images, trekker expects at the following inputs to be specified:
.INDENT 0.0
.IP \(bu 2
trekker generates streamlines from a fiber orientation distribution (FOD) image provided by the user with the option \fI\-fod\fP\&.
.IP \(bu 2
trekker expects the user to provide a seed image with the option \fI\-seed_image\fP or a list of seed coordinates with the option \fI\-seed_coordinates\fP\&.
.IP \(bu 2
If a seed image is provided, the user can provide the number of streamlines to be generated either with the option \fI\-seed_count\fP or \fI\-seed_countPerVoxel\fP\&. If \fI\-seed_coordinates\fP options is used, trekker will generate one streamline for each specified coordinate. Alternatively the \fI\-timeLimit\fP option can be used to stop tracking after a certain amount of time.
.IP \(bu 2
Lastly the user has to provide the output path with \fI\-output\fP followed by the path and name of the output file. trekker’s output file format is *.vtk. An additional .json formatted metadata is also saved.
.IP \(bu 2
All unspecified parameters will be set to trekker’s default values.
.UNINDENT
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.nf
.ft C
# Example 1
\&./trekker \-fod FOD.nii.gz \e
          \-seed_image SEED.nii.gz \e
          \-seed_count 1000 \e
          \-output OUTPUT.vtk
.ft P
.fi
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.nf
.ft C
# Example 2
\&./trekker \-fod FOD.nii.gz \e
          \-seed_coordinates COORDINATES \e
          \-output OUTPUT.vtk
.ft P
.fi
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.nf
.ft C
# Example 3
\&./trekker \-fod FOD.nii.gz \e
          \-seed_image SEED.nii.gz \e
          \-timeLimit 15 \e # time limit is in minutes
          \-output OUTPUT.vtk
.ft P
.fi
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.SH OPTIONS
.SS Tracking options
.sp
\fB\-fod <nifti image>\fP Path to FOD image. Accepted file extensions are: nii, nii.gz. FOD contains \fI\%spherical harmonics coefficients\fP\&. Only even degreed FODs are supported. Each coefficient should be stored as a separate volume in the following order with respect to spherical harmonic degree, l and m (i.e: MRtrix convention):
.SS The format of the FOD image
.TS
center;
|l|l|l|l|l|l|l|l|l|l|l|.
